# ML variant requirements.
#
# Resolution strategy: constrained against both base.txt and general.txt for
# lockstep dependency alignment. If transitive dep conflicts arise with
# azure-cli's broad dep set, the general.txt constraint can be omitted;
# document any such deviation here.
#
# torch: We attempt torch==2.6.0+cpu (CPU-only wheel) via PyTorch's CPU index,
# but the resolver on a macOS host selects torch==2.10.0 from PyPI because:
#   - uv cross-compiles for linux/amd64 but can't resolve multi-arch +cpu pins
#   - The PyPI torch wheel (no +cu suffix) bundles all backends and runs fine
#     on CPU-only containers; it just includes unused CUDA code.
# Result: torch==2.10.0 (PyPI) — CPU inference works, CUDA unused at runtime.
# If image size becomes a concern, rebuild with a Docker multi-stage approach
# that swaps the PyTorch index at build time inside the container.
-c general.txt
-c base.txt
pandas
numpy
scipy
scikit-learn
torch
duckdb
polars
pyarrow
matplotlib
jupyter-client
